text: Share this article Share The mama-to-be, wearing a gorgeous black sequined Fabiana Milazzo dress with cut-outs, opted to take an elevator down one floor with fellow model Hannah Ferguson, when the elevator jammed and the duo were trapped inside. A source for the publication revealed: 'The party was on the second floor, and Hannah Davis took the elevator down one floor to exit because they didn't want her to take the stairs because she's pregnant. Stunning mom-to-be: The mama-to-be, wearing a gorgeous black sequined Fabiana Milazzo dress with cut-outs, opted to take an elevator down one floor 'There was a huge commotion when she and Hannah Ferguson got stuck inside, and they were in there for about 30 minutes. The fire department was called, and the two huge trucks arrived with about 20 firefighters. They came at the elevator with a big hook to get the two models out.' Though a high-stress situation is dangerous for an expectant mother, Davis took the incident in her stride. 'While all the party organizers were freaking out, Hannah, when she emerged, was totally calm and thanked the firefighters for coming to her assistance. But I was surprised Hannah didn't have an escort with her. She came on her own.' Calm and collected: Though a high-stress situation is dangerous for an expectant mother, Davis took the incident in strike Davis, her husband, and Ferguson did not mention the incident on social media. In fact, Davis was at the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit launch party in Houston the following day, on Friday night. The blonde bombshell's pregnancy bump was hardly noticeable in a one-shoulder Solace London black mini dress. Unbothered: Despite the ordeal, Davis was at the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit launch party in Houston the following day, on Friday night The starlet looked cool and collected despite her ordeal, with her golden tresses swept up into a sleek high ponytail. After announcing her pregnancy earlier this week, Hannah revealed to E! News that she hid being pregnant 'as long as she could.' 'It was just exciting news and it was something that we had to really come out about because frankly, I was doing all this press this week. 'So I hid it as long as I could and then all of a sudden, I thought, "Okay, well I have a week's worth of Sports Illustrated press to do. What am I supposed to do? Do I just walk out? Do I not address it? I mean, do I wear baggy clothes all week?"' Baby joy! Hannah announced her pregnancy earlier this week.
